Fuller Length, outside off stump, Boyden lines up the drive and edges through to keeper Bana, who pouches his fourth catch of the game! Ravi Kumar bags 4 wickets, with Kaushal Tambe picking up 1. James Rew top scored for England with 95. India need 190 to win the ICC U19 Men's World Cup 2022.

A top effort with the ball from India to bowl out England for 189 after Tom Prest opted to bat first. Ravi Kumar (4/34) did early damage to England's top order, while Raj Bawa's (5/31) superb spell reduced England to 91/7. Thereafter, James Rew (95 from 116b) and James Sales (34* from 65b) combined for a 93-run 8th wicket stand, before once again the pacers combined to bowl out England for the first time in this tournament.
